features: 【Better Protection】LEVENIS Ventilation Series KN95 Face Masks follow the GB2626-2019 respiratory protection standards, equipped with a new generation of high protection melt blown filters, typically feature a filtration efficiency of over 95%.

【Lightweight】LEVENIS KN95 Face Masks are designed to be lightweight, making them comfortable and breathable to wear for extended periods. Despite their lightweight, they still provide the high level of protection.

【Ergonomically Designed】 LEVENIS KN95 Face Masks is designed ergonomically to ensure that it can fully adhere to your face, nose, mouth, and chin. Provide you with the most comfortable wearing experience.

【Skin-friendly】These LEVENIS KN95 face masks features two layers of skin friendly non-woven fabric on the outer layer and two layers of high-quality melt blown filters on the inner layer. Allowing you to be protected without worrying about damaging your skin.
【Disclaimer】This KN95 mask is NOT an N95 mask. For more information about KN95 masks please see the following before you purchase: amazon.com/AboutKN95s.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This face masks are exceptional! They provide a secure and comfortable fit, ensuring reliable protection. The quality of the materials is evident, and I appreciate the attention to detail in their design. These masks offer peace of mind in challenging times, and I highly recommend them for their comfort, effectiveness, and overall quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit snug to face
reviews.reviewText: I am a teacher, with classroom sizes of up to 75 students. With that many people in a room, there is usually at least one person who is sick with something. I don't have the luxury of dropping lectures, which means I need to make sure I stay healthy.These masks work really well, for me. They fit snug to my face without the air gaps around the edges that some of the other masks have left me with. That said, they do not fit my son as well (he's a lot skinnier than I am). I wear glasses, so these do fog my glasses to a certain extent. I have found that on days where I also need to wear safety goggles and the mask (and my glasses), it helps if I trim a little of the mask around the eye area. That still leaves the mask fitting well, but does cut down of the fogging of the goggles.I have rarely had one of the ear elastic bands snap. When that does happen, it happens right away when I am putting the mask on, not during the course of the day. I generally have days of 6+ hours of wearing the mask with minimal discomfort.I recommend these for larger faced individuals, and those who have to wear a mask for extended periods of time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Maybe my face is more sensitive than others, but the inside is a bit itchy and rough. Definitely has a smell when first opening the package, but does dissipate. These aren't my favorite masks and now I wish I hadn't bought the 100 pack! Overall I do like the shape, but I definitely would not buy these again. They're also a bit more flimsy than the mask brand I previously purchased but can no longer find.They work in a pinch, but not my favorite by far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Seams pull apart easily
reviews.reviewText: Update: The review below is still valid for the batch that I received. I had not reported my concerns to the company and was not expecting a response, but they reached out to me (via Amazon) based on this review and have attempted to make it right. An extra star for very good customer service.----------I wanted to like these for the style, level of protection, and convenience of the ear loops. However, the seam attaching the bottom third of the mask pulls apart with the slightest effort. Even if you manage to get it on your face without pulling apart, just moving your jaw while talking or definitely yawning will begin to pull the seam apart. (Interestingly, the top seam is very sturdy even with moderate pulling.) It has been true for all of the masks I’ve tested. This of course makes the masks useless.It’s possible that I got a bad batch, but several other reviewers have indicated the same problem, so it’s clear their quality control is very poor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a very comfortable mask. Soft and pliable but strong. Doesn’t come to a beak like some do. Has a nice flat surface with plenty of room.
